# Plan of Action & Milestones (POA&M) Summary

## Executive Overview

This Plan of Action and Milestones (POA&M) document identifies 10 high-priority security control remediation items designed to address vulnerabilities exploited by nation-state Advanced Persistent Threat (APT) groups targeting U.S. defense and critical infrastructure sectors. All identified weaknesses are directly mapped to MITRE ATT&CK techniques used by **APT29 (Russia)**, **Volt Typhoon (China)**, and **APT33 (Iran)**.

**Project Metadata:**
- **Name:** Ryan Verrot
- **System:** Course Project: Part Two
- **Impact Level:** High
- **POA&M Date:** May 3, 2026
- **Total Open Items:** 10
- **Risk Rating:** All High Priority

