## Prioritization Methodology

### **Risk-Based Control Selection**

Controls were prioritized based on:

1. **Technique Prevalence:** How many APT groups exploit each technique
2. **Attack Path Criticality:** Position in the attack lifecycle (Initial Access → Privilege Escalation → Lateral Movement → Exfiltration)
3. **Implementation Feasibility:** Time and resource requirements for remediation
4. **Organizational Impact:** Business process disruption vs. security benefit

### **MITRE ATT&CK Mapping**

All 10 controls are mapped to the five **High-Risk techniques** (used by all 3 APT groups):

| MITRE ATT&CK Technique | Technique ID | APT Groups | Controls Addressing |
|------------------------|--------------|-----------|-------------------|
| **Valid Accounts** | T1078 | All 3 | AC-06, IA-02, AC-02 |
| **Command and Scripting Interpreter** | T1059 | All 3 | CM-07, SI-04, AC-06, CM-06, SI-03 |
| **Exploit Public-Facing Application** | T1190 | All 3 | CM-07, SI-04, CM-06, SC-07, RA-05 |
| **File and Directory Discovery** | T1083 | All 3 | CM-07, AC-06, AC-02 |
| **Ingress Tool Transfer** | T1105 | All 3 | CM-07, CM-06, SC-07, SI-03 |

