## Key Findings from Threat Analysis

### **Why These Controls Matter**

**APT29 (Russia) - SolarWinds Supply Chain Attack:**
- **Attack Path:** Exploit Public-Facing Application (T1190) → Ingress Tool Transfer (T1105) → Command Execution (T1059) → Privilege Escalation → Persistent Backdoor
- **Addressed By:** CM-07, SI-04, CA-07, SC-07, RA-05

**Volt Typhoon (China) - Critical Infrastructure Targeting:**
- **Attack Path:** Exploit Public-Facing Application (T1190) → Valid Accounts (T1078) → Living off the Land (T1059) → Lateral Movement → Pre-positioning for Disruption
- **Addressed By:** SC-07, IA-02, AC-06, SI-04, CM-06

**APT33 (Iran) - Aerospace & Defense Targeting:**
- **Attack Path:** Phishing → Password Spraying (T1110 → T1078) → Valid Accounts Compromise → File Discovery (T1083) → Data Exfiltration
- **Addressed By:** IA-02, AC-02, AC-06, CM-07, SI-04

